{
 "name": "RPlog_Of_Ships_and_Sentients_Butchers_and_Arrivals_-_part_1",
 "title": "Of Ships and Sentients, Butchers and Arrivals (Part 1)",
 "summary": "In the engineering compartment of the Caspian warship CMS Audace, the doctor-commander Lynae Cassius confers with the Twi'lek engineer Ven Secura about a power-fluctuation glitch introduced by a recent refit, now repaired. Their technical conversation turns philosophical when Lynae mentions an augmented, sentient industrial droid, touching a raw nerve in Ven, a former slave who reacts viscerally to talk of ownership and slavery. Lynae draws him out on the meaning of home, belonging, and the choices that make a place one's own, and the young engineer finds unexpected resonance in her views before duty calls him away. The exchange establishes Lynae's thoughtful, humanizing leadership style aboard the Audace.",
